    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon selected" style="background-image:url('/images/metalroof.jpg')" id="metal">
        Metal
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/tiledroof.jpg')">
        Tiles
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  

  <div class="row">
    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/concreteroof.jpg')">
        Concrete
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/asphaltroof.jpg')">
        Asphalt
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="row">
    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/fibreglassroof.jpg')">
        Fibreglass
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="columns small-6">
      <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/slateroof.jpg')">
        Slate
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="row">
   <div class="columns small-6">
     <div class="material_icon" style="background-image:url('/images/asbestosroof.jpg')">
       Asbestos
     </div>
   </div>

   <div class="columns small-6">
     <div class="material_icon">
       Unknown
     </div>
   </div>
  </div>

  <button class="button expand" onclick="show('pageEight');">OK, next</button>
  
  <div class="info_icon">
    <a href="#" data-reveal-id="material_info" id="shade_button"><img class="info-icon" src="/images/info_sign.png"></a>
  </div>

  <div id="material_info" class="reveal-modal info-popup" data-reveal>
    <p>“What the roof is made out of can really affect how easy it is to install panels on. Steel is best, tiles are usually OK, asbestos is bad news. And if the roof is thatched? Forget it.”</p>
    <a class="close-reveal-modal">&#215;</a>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- Page Eight -->
<div class="page" id="pageEight">
  <div class="row"> 
    <div class="columns">
      <h4>
        Is there anything around that could cast a shadow on the roof? 
        Use the slider to record the shading.
      </h4>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <br>
  

  <div class="row">
    <div class="columns">
      <output class="chunky" id="shade">50%</output>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="columns">
      <img src="/images/img_shade.png">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="large-6 medium-8 small-12 large-centered medium-centered small-centered column">
        <input type="range" class="slider-properties" id="shader" min="0" max="100" step="10" name="shade_value" onchange="outputUpdate(value)">
        <button class="button expand bottom" id="toPageNine" onclick="show('pageNine');">Next</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="info_icon">
    <a href="#" data-reveal-id="shade_info" id="shade_button"><img class="info-icon" src="/images/info_sign.png"></a>
  </div>

  <div id="shade_info" class="reveal-modal info-popup" data-reveal>
    <p>“Shading can make all the difference to a roof’s potential, and even a little bit of shading - for instance, like the thin shadow cast by overhead phone cables - can be a big problem for solar panels’ power output. Watch out for things like nearby buildings and trees, and chimneys or air conditioning units on the roof in question. Shading will be different at different times of day, so it’s hard to get this right during a spot check. Just give it your best guess for now.”</p>
    <a class="close-reveal-modal">&#215;</a>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Page nine -->

<div class="page" id="pageNine">

  <style>
    html, body, #map-canvas {
      height: 400px;
      width: 100%;
    }
  </style>

  <div>Here’s your roof – let’s measure it!</div>
  <div id="map-canvas"></div>
  <div id="1st_text">First, drag the the pins to draw a line down one edge of the roof.</div>
  <div id="2nd_text">Now draw a new line across the other edge.</div>


  <input type="hidden" id="angled" placeholder="Angled Edge" name="angled_edge" value="0">
  <button id="btn-angled" class="button expand bottom">Measure angled edge</button>
  <input type="hidden" id="gutter" placeholder="Gutter Edge" name="gutter_edge" value="0">
  <input id="btn-gutter" class="button expand bottom" value="Now measure gutter edge" onclick="show('pageTen');">
</div>

